  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 4 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 4 high, 6 medium, 28 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Poznań-Ławica (POZ/EPPO); plus 2 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and RVR limitations  — most notably around London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), London Luton (LTN/EGGW) and Poznań-Ławica (POZ/EPPO). Network hotspots: Beauvais Tillé (BVA/LFOB), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Birmingham (BHX/EGBB), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK). Primary drivers: mist, very low visibility and fog / freezing fog. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Birmingham (BHX/EGBB), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), Billund (BLL/EKBI) and 9 others.",
